Mapped polygons represent a range of soil types. The site lies in the North Pennine uplands of England and has an area of 74 km2. It is England's highest and largest terrestrial National Nature Reserve (NNR), a UNESCO Biosphere Reserve and a European Special Protection Area. Habitats include exposed summits, extensive blanket peatlands, upland grasslands, pastures, hay meadows and deciduous woodland. Altitude ranges from 290 to 850 m. Moor House - Upper Teesdale is part of the Environmental Change Network (ECN) whcih is the UK's long-term environmental monitoring programme. </dcterms:description>     <dcterms:modified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2015-01-14T14:52:07Z</dcterms:modified>     <dcterms:creator>asowe</dcterms:creator>     <dcterms:title xml:lang="en">Soil map of the Moor House National Nature Reserve</dcterms:title>     <dcterms:hasPart>       <file:File rdf:about="http://eidchub.ceh.ac.uk/metadata/b36357bd-988c-41fa-a3a8-3b21cef5f0b6/data_documenation_moorhouse_soil">         <dcterms:description xml:lang="en">Supporting documentation to help in the use of the Soil map for Moor House National Nature Reserve dataset</dcterms:description>         <dcterms:modified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2013-07-12T10:58:51Z</dcterms:modified>         <dcterms:creator>asowe</dcterms:creator>         <dcterms:title xml:lang="en">Data_documenation_MoorHouse_Soil</dcterms:title>         <dcterms:isPartOf rdf:resource="http://eidchub.ceh.ac.uk/metadata/b36357bd-988c-41fa-a3a8-3b21cef5f0b6"/>         <dcterms:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2013-07-12T10:58:50Z</dcterms:created>         <file:id xml:lang="en">data_documenation_moorhouse_soil</file:id>       </file:File>     </dcterms:hasPart>     <dcterms:hasPart>       <file:File rdf:about="http://eidchub.ceh.ac.uk/metadata/b36357bd-988c-41fa-a3a8-3b21cef5f0b6/johnson_dunham">         <dcterms:description xml:lang="en">Chapter 15 from Johnson and Dunham (1963) The geology of Moor House, a National Nature Reserve in North East Westmorland.
